<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple Crisp</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Desserts</cat>
        <cat>Fruits</cat></categories>
      <yield>6</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>C&amp;H Golden Brown Sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>All-purpose flour</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Nutmeg</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Cinnamon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Butter or margarine</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>5</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Sliced tart apples (5 to 6 apples)</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Mix sugar, flour, spices, and salt.  Cut in butter until mixture is
  crumbly.  Spread apples in bottom of buttered 8- or 9-inch square baking
  pan.  Sprinkle crumbly mixture over fruit; pat lightly with fingers.  Bake
  uncovered at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes, or until apples are tender.
  Serve warm with cream or ice cream.  Makes 6 to 8 servings.
  
